        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "Launched on 13th December 2016, the &quot;Incentive Scheme for Establishment of New Super Specialty Hospital in Private Sector&quot; by the Health &amp; Family Welfare Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to address the shortage of high-end medical facilities in remote areas by incentivizing private and non-governmental organizations to establish super specialty hospitals. The scheme provides 10% capital subsidy on medical equipment loans (up to ₹10 crore), 4% interest subvention (max ₹40 crore loan) for 7 years, and reimbursement of electricity duty for 5 years. Eligible entities include registered doctors, firms, trusts, and corporations.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Capital Subsidy**\n\n\n- 10% of bank loans for medical equipment (max ₹10 crore).\n- Disbursed post-hospital operationalization.\n\n> **Interest Subvention**\n\n\n- 4% interest relief on loans up to ₹40 crore for 7 years.\n- Paid in 6 annual installments after a 1-year grace period.\n\n> **Electricity Duty Reimbursement**\n\n100% reimbursement for 5 years (quarterly claims).\n> **Employment Generation**\n\nMandates hiring qualified medical/paramedical staff.\n> **Disbursement**\n\n\n- **Capital Subsidy:** After Equipment Installation and Hospital Launch.- **Interest Subvention:** Annual Installments Post 1-Year Grace Period.- **Electricity Reimbursement:** Quarterly Claims.\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "Excludes Government/Semi-Government Bodies.\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme offers financial incentives (capital subsidy, interest subvention, and electricity duty reimbursement) to private/NGO entities establishing new super specialty hospitals (50+ beds) in Gujarat, targeting underserved areas.",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Launched on 13th December 2016, the \"Incentive Scheme for Establishment of New Super Specialty Hospital in Private Sector\" by the Health & Family Welfare Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to address the shortage of high-end medical facilities in remote areas by incentivizing private and non-governmental organizations to establish super specialty hospitals. The scheme provides 10% capital subsidy on medical equipment loans (up to ₹10 crore), 4% interest subvention (max ₹40 crore loan) for 7 years, and reimbursement of electricity duty for 5 years. Eligible entities include registered doctors, firms, trusts, and corporations."
              }
